io.confluent.ksql.rest.server.execution

Interface StatementExecutor<T extends Statement>

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface StatementExecutor<T extends Statement>
    An interface that allows for arbitrary execution code of a prepared statement.

      • execute

        java.util.Optional<KsqlEntity> execute(ConfiguredStatement<T> statement,
                                       SessionProperties sessionProperties,
                                       KsqlExecutionContext executionContext,
                                       ServiceContext serviceContext)
        Executes the query against the parameterized ksqlEngine.
        Parameters:
        statement - the statement to execute
        sessionProperties - the session properties
        executionContext - the context in which to execute it
        serviceContext - the services to use to execute it
        Returns:
        the execution result, if present, else Optional.empty()
